---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import { glossaryArticles } from '../../data/glossary';
---

<Base title="Glossary Definitions">
  <main class="py-16 md:py-32">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-4">
      {/* Page header */}
      <div class="mb-16">
        <h1 class="font-heading text-4xl md:text-5xl text-text font-normal">
          Glossary Definitions
        </h1>
        <div class="font-body text-base text-muted mt-4 space-y-4 max-w-xl leading-[1.7]">
          <p>
            I produced 75 technical glossary definitions for Azul Systems with no prior technical background, independently teaching myself Java and cloud infrastructure concepts to write accessible, example-led content for an audience of DevOps engineers and financial stakeholders. I developed all product tie-ins for each definition, identifying the most relevant Azul use cases for each concept and integrating SEO terms throughout to strengthen reach. The work generated 115K impressions within 3 months, strengthening Azul's SEO presence in the Java developer community.
          </p>
          <p>Below is a curated selection of technical concepts from my work.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      {/* Article list */}
      <div>
        {glossaryArticles.map((article) => (
          <article
            key={article.slug}
            class="border-t border-border py-8 first:border-t-0 first:pt-0"
          >
            <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-normal text-text">
              {article.title}
            </h2>
            {article.excerpt && (
              <p class="font-body text-base text-muted mt-2">{article.excerpt}</p>
            )}
            <p class="font-body text-sm text-muted mt-1">
              {article.company} · {article.period}
            </p>
            <a
              href={`/glossary/${article.slug}`}
              class="font-body text-sm font-semibold text-text hover:underline mt-3 block"
            >
              Read →
            </a>
          </article>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Base>
